The Macao Garrison of the Chinese People's Liberation Army in early Thursday morning conducted the 20th rotation of its members since it began garrisoning Macao in 1999. Approved by the Central Military Commission, the move is normal routine annual rotation in line with the Law of the People's Republic of China on Garrisoning the Macao Special Administrative Region. 
